  "text": "The subsidence of the TB was associated with the accumulation of clayey fill in the Martin Formation and the development of planation surfaces which are actually preserved in the central parts of all the surrounding mountains (Figs. 5, 12: 'Mid-mountain level'). The results of AFT thermal modelling confirm thermal stability in the Malá Fatra Mts [CITATION_1] ) and also most likely in the Žiar Mts [CITATION_2] .",
